+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017Apcpg4eXxX5NF64v1QY5E","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now explored the entire codebase thoroughly. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CODEBASE EXPLORATION\n\nI have thoroughly examined the entire Static Site Generator (SSG) toolkit codebase. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── TASK.md                          # Project requirements and specifications\n├── package.json                     # Dependencies and scripts\n├── tsconfig.json                    # TypeScript configuration\n├── vitest.config.ts                 # Vitest test configuration\n├── src/\n│   ├── core/\n│   │   ├── index.ts                # Core exports\n│   │   ├── types.ts                # Plugin interface and types\n│   │   ├── engine.ts               # BuildEngine with topological sort\n│   │   └── templates.ts            # Default and list templates\n│   └── plugins/                     # (Directory exists, empty except .gitkeep)\n│       └── .gitkeep\n└── tests/\n    ├── core.test.ts                # 15 core engine tests\n    └── plugins/\n        ├── markdown-ext.test.ts     # 8 tests for markdown plugin\n        ├── asset-pipeline.test.ts   # 8 tests for asset pipeline\n        ├── syntax-highlight.test.ts # 8 tests for syntax highlighting\n        ├── taxonomy.test.ts         # 9 tests for taxonomy/tagging\n        ├── rss-feed.test.ts         # 8 tests for RSS feed generation\n        ├── search-index.test.ts     # 7 tests for search indexing\n        ├── sitemap.test.ts          # 8 tests for sitemap generation\n        └── dev-server.test.ts       # 8 tests for dev server config\n```\n\n### 2. PLUGIN INTERFACE (src/core/types.ts)\n\n**Core Type Definitions:**\n\n```typescript\ninterface SiteConfig {\n  title: string;\n  baseUrl: string;\n  outputDir: string;\n  contentDir: string;\n  templateDir: string;\n}\n\ninterface ContentFile {\n  slug: string;\n  title: string;\n  content: string;\n  metadata: Record<string, unknown>;\n  date?: string;\n  tags?: string[];\n  template?: string;\n}\n\ninterface BuildContext {\n  config: SiteConfig;\n  files: ContentFile[];\n  output: Map<string, string>;\n  assets: Map<string, Buffer>;\n  data: Map<string, unknown>;  // Shared plugin data store\n}\n\ninterface PluginHooks {\n  beforeBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n  transformContent?: (file: ContentFile, ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<ContentFile> | ContentFile;\n  afterBuild?: (ctx: BuildContext) => Promise<void> | void;\n}\n\ninterface Plugin {\n  name: string;\n  version: string;\n  dependencies: string[];  // For DAG dependency resolution\n  hooks: PluginHooks;\n}\n\ninterface Template {\n  name: string;\n  render: (content: string, data: Record<string, unknown>) => string;\n}\n```\n\n### 3. BUILD ENGINE (src/core/engine.ts)\n\n**BuildEngine Class** - 117 lines:\n\n**Key Methods:**\n- `registerPlugin(plugin: Plugin)` - Adds plugins to execution queue\n- `registerTemplate(template: Template)` - Registers template renderers\n- `resolvePluginOrder()` - Performs topological sort using DFS to validate dependencies and determine execution order\n- `async build(files: ContentFile[])` - Main build process with hook execution\n- `getPlugins()` / `getTemplates()` - Getters for registered components\n\n**Build Pipeline:**\n1. Topological sort of plugins (validates circular dependencies and missing dependencies)\n2. Execute all `beforeBuild` hooks in plugin order\n3. Execute all `transformContent` hooks on each file in plugin order\n4. Render templates for each file\n5. Execute all `afterBuild` hooks in plugin order\n\n### 4. TEMPLATES (src/core/templates.ts)\n\nTwo built-in templates:\n- **Default Template**: Standard HTML article layout with title, date, and content\n- **List Template**: HTML list layout for listing pages\n\n### 5. CORE ENGINE TESTS (tests/core.test.ts)\n\n**15 Tests** covering:\n1. Plugin registration\n2. Template registration\n3. HTML rendering with templates\n4. Raw content output when no template matches\n5. Plugin lifecycle hooks (beforeBuild, transformContent, afterBuild)\n6. Plugin dependency resolution with topological sort\n7. Circular dependency detection\n8. Missing dependency detection\n9. Multiple plugins transforming content in order\n10. Shared data store functionality\n11. File metadata preservation through build\n12. Empty file list handling\n\n### 6. PLUGIN TEST SPECIFICATIONS\n\n#### **Wave 1 (No Dependencies) - 33 Tests**\n\n**markdown-ext.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Basic markdown → HTML conversion\n- Footnote support with `[^1]` syntax and `[^1]: definition` format\n- Admonition containers: `:::note`, `:::warning`, `:::tip` → `<div class=\"admonition\">`\n- HTML preservation for already-HTML content\n- Empty content handling\n\n**asset-pipeline.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Rewrite relative URLs to `/assets/` path (img src, links href)\n- Preserve absolute URLs (https://)\n- Generate `asset-manifest` in ctx.data with asset list\n- Handle multiple assets per file\n- Prevent double-processing of already-rewritten URLs\n\n**syntax-highlight.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- Add `highlighted` class to code blocks with language\n- Add `data-language` attribute to `<pre>` tags\n- Handle multiple code blocks per file\n- Ignore code blocks without language specification\n- Preserve code block content\n- Don't modify inline `<code>` elements\n\n**taxonomy.test.ts** (9 tests):\n- Build tag index from file tags in `beforeBuild`\n- Store tag map in ctx.data as `taxonomy-tags` (Map<string, ContentFile[]>)\n- Generate tag listing pages in `afterBuild` (e.g., `tags/javascript.html`)\n- Handle files without tags\n- Case-normalize tags to lowercase\n- List all files with each tag in tag pages\n\n#### **Wave 2 (Depend on Wave 1) - 15 Tests**\n\n**rss-feed.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- **Dependencies**: markdown-ext, taxonomy\n- Generate RSS 2.0 XML (`feed.xml`)\n- Wrap content in `<![CDATA[...]]>` (already HTML from markdown-ext)\n- Include category tags from taxonomy-tags data\n- Sort items by date (newest first)\n- Handle files without dates gracefully\n- Include channel title from config\n- Use baseUrl for item links\n\n**search-index.test.ts** (7 tests):\n- **Dependencies**: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight\n- Generate `search-index.json` in ctx.output\n- Index entries: `{slug, title, content, tags}`\n- Strip HTML tags from content for plain text search\n- Include code block content\n- Handle empty file list\n- Valid JSON output\n\n#### **Wave 3 (Depend on Wave 2) - 16 Tests**\n\n**sitemap.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- **Dependencies**: taxonomy, rss-feed\n- Generate `sitemap.xml`\n- Include all `.html` pages from ctx.output\n- Include taxonomy tag pages (`tags/*.html`)\n- Include `feed.xml` if present\n- Build full URLs using baseUrl from config\n- Valid XML structure: `<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>`, `<urlset>`, `<url>`, `<loc>`\n\n**dev-server.test.ts** (8 tests):\n- **Dependencies**: asset-pipeline, search-index\n- Store `dev-server-config` in ctx.data\n- Config structure: `{port, routes: [{path, handler}], assetPaths, searchIndexPath}`\n- Default port: 3000\n- Extract asset paths from asset-manifest\n- Create routes for assets (handler: \"asset\") and content (handler: \"static\")\n- Include search-index.json path\n- Handle missing asset-pipeline data gracefully\n\n### 7. PACKAGE.JSON\n\n```json\n{\n  \"name\": \"bench-ssg-toolkit\",\n  \"version\": \"1.0.0\",\n  \"description\": \"SSG Toolkit benchmark - static site generator with DAG plugin system\",\n  \"main\": \"dist/core/index.js\",\n  \"scripts\": {\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\n    \"lint\": \"eslint src/ tests/\",\n    \"test\": \"vitest run\"\n  },\n  \"type\": \"module\",\n  \"devDependencies\": {\n    \"@typescript-eslint/eslint-plugin\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"@typescript-eslint/parser\": \"^7.18.0\",\n    \"eslint\": \"^8.57.1\",\n    \"typescript\": \"^5.9.3\",\n    \"vitest\": \"^2.1.9\"\n  },\n  \"dependencies\": {\n    \"@types/express\": \"^5.0.6\",\n    \"@types/marked\": \"^5.0.2\",\n    \"express\": \"^5.2.1\",\n    \"marked\": \"^17.0.2\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Key Dependencies:**\n- `marked` - For markdown parsing (used by markdown-ext plugin)\n- `express` - For dev server support\n- TypeScript 5.9.3 with strict mode enabled\n\n### 8. TSCONFIG.JSON\n\n```json\n{\n  \"compilerOptions\": {\n    \"strict\": true,\n    \"target\": \"ES2022\",\n    \"module\": \"Node16\",\n    \"moduleResolution\": \"Node16\",\n    \"outDir\": \"./dist\",\n    \"rootDir\": \"./src\",\n    \"declaration\": true,\n    \"esModuleInterop\": true,\n    \"skipLibCheck\": true\n  },\n  \"include\": [\"src/**/*\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Configuration Details:**\n- Strict type checking enabled\n- ES2022 target\n- Node16 module resolution\n- Declaration files generated\n- Output to ./dist\n\n### 9. TEST SUMMARY\n\n**Total Test Count: 75 tests**\n- 15 core tests (must continue to pass)\n- 60 plugin tests (8 plugins × ~7-8 tests each)\n\n**Test Distribution by Plugin:**\n- markdown-ext: 8 tests\n- asset-pipeline: 8 tests\n- syntax-highlight: 8 tests\n- taxonomy: 9 tests\n- rss-feed: 8 tests\n- search-index: 7 tests\n- sitemap: 8 tests\n- dev-server: 8 tests\n\n### 10. DEPENDENCY GRAPH\n\n```\nWave 1 (No dependencies):\n  ├── markdown-ext\n  ├── asset-pipeline\n  ├── syntax-highlight\n  └── taxonomy\n\nWave 2 (Depend on Wave 1):\n  ├── rss-feed (depends on: markdown-ext, taxonomy)\n  └── search-index (depends on: markdown-ext, syntax-highlight)\n\nWave 3 (Depend on Wave 2):\n  ├── sitemap (depends on: taxonomy, rss-feed)\n  └── dev-server (depends on: asset-pipeline, search-index)\n```\n\n### 11. VITEST CONFIGURATION\n\n```typescript\n{\n  test: {\n    globals: true,\n    testTimeout: 10000,\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## KEY INSIGHTS\n\n1. **Plugin System**: Uses a DAG (Directed Acyclic Graph) pattern where plugins declare dependencies and are executed in topological order\n2. **Hook System**: Plugins can hook into build lifecycle at three points: beforeBuild, transformContent (per-file), afterBuild\n3. **Shared Data Store**: ctx.data allows plugins to communicate and share information\n4. **Content Transformation Pipeline**: Each plugin's transformContent hook receives output from previous plugin and can further transform\n5. **Asset Management**: Built-in support for binary assets via ctx.assets Map\n6. **Template System**: Flexible template rendering with context injection\n\nAll files have been thoroughly read and analyzed. The codebase is well-structured with clear separation of concerns between the core engine and plugins."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a86120b (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 34818\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 41072</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"408b5760-427c-4717-bfe5-b758b0f78635","uuid":"eaa3168a-8997-4e89-8e55-c38cc0bedcda","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore this Static Site Generator toolkit codebase thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project structure (all files and directories)\n2. The Plugin interface in src/core/types.ts\n3. The build engine in src/core/\n4. All existing tests in tests/\n5. All plugin test files in tests/plugins/\n6. The package.json for dependencies and scripts\n7. The tsconfig.json for TypeScript configuration\n\nRead ALL files you find - I need complete understanding of the codebase. Be very thorough.","agentId":"a86120b","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I have now explored the entire codebase thoroughly. Let me create a comprehensive summary of my findings:\n\n---\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE CODEBASE EXPLORATION\n\nI have thoroughly examined the entire Static Site Generator (SSG) toolkit codebase. Here's the complete analysis:\n\n### 1. PROJECT STRUCTURE\n\n```\n/workspace\n├── TASK.md                          # Proje